  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (theory-preconditions gap)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The hemolysis power-law model (Giersiepen–Wurzinger correlation) is applied under the explicit theoretical precondition that blood damage accumulation is linear and time-additive along streamlines — i.e., the scalar damage index D = integral(sigma^a * t^b) is valid only when shear stress exposure is monotonically increasing and the fluid parcels are non-recirculating. No validation result in this package verifies that the CPB pump operating regime satisfies this linearity-and-no-recirculation precondition.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
