      "name": "Relative hemolysis index comparison against predicate device",
      "description": "Computed RH index for the FDA generic pump compared against the predicate device hemolysis measurements at matched operating conditions. RH = 0.83 (< 1.0 acceptance criterion). Giersiepen–Wurzinger power-law coefficients alpha=0.785, beta=0.062, C=1.8e-6 used as published. No assessment of whether the linear damage accumulation assumption holds for the recirculating flow regimes present in the volute.",
