      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation setup reviewed by independent analyst; boundary conditions and material properties traceable to documented sources.",
      "rationale": "Independent analyst reviewed mesh, boundary conditions, turbulence model selection, and post-processing scripts. No errors identified. Material properties sourced from published literature with traceability. Required level 1 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Governing equation set (turbulence model, hemolysis correlation) justified for the flow regime and documented.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on best agreement with PIV data among three candidate models. Giersiepen–Wurzinger power-law hemolysis correlation adopted as the regulatory standard approach. Model form uncertainty acknowledged. The correlation's theoretical precondition — that damage accumulates linearly and independently of flow history along each streamline — is stated in the model documentation but is not verified for the COU geometry, where recirculating vortices in the volute may violate path-independence. Required level 2 assessed as achieved based on correlation agreement with bench data alone."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
