    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou1-decision-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for Model Risk Level 2. Six factors are not assessed, consistent with MRL 2 requirements per ASME V&V 40. The CFD model predicts RH = 0.83, satisfying the RH < 1 acceptance criterion. Mesh convergence, solver verification, and velocity field validation provide sufficient evidence of simulation credibility for the intended regulatory submission. The Giersiepen–Wurzinger hemolysis model is accepted as the regulatory standard approach; its theoretical precondition of linear, path-independent damage accumulation is noted in the model form rationale and considered acceptable given agreement with bench hemolysis reference data.",
